node.messageHeadline: TST:  Fix sqlite3 transactions test (#28450)
node.message:
TST:  Fix sqlite3 transactions test (#28450)

The sqlite connection is already in transaction when the test starts, so
when the test intentionally raises an exception, the entire transaction,
including the table creation, gets rolled back, so there is no table
to query.  Wrapping the table CREATE statement in its own transaction
avoids the issue.

node.messageHeadline: Fix a typo in "computation.rst" in document. (#28400)
node.message:
Fix a typo in "computation.rst" in document. (#28400)

There's `np.random.np.random` in /doc/source/user_guide/computation.rst, which I believe is a typo. But the weird thing is there's actually `np.random.np` in numpy (1.16.4), but not in numpy (1.17.2). That's maybe why the doc build passed before. While I'm trying to build the doc locally with numpy 1.17.2, it failed.
